  "body": "<!--NOTE: -->\r\n<!--- General questions should go to the discord chat instead of the issue tracker.-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug**\r\n\r\nWe currently expect to receive a response from Goodbye requestes. We also expect our peer to receive our goodbye response. As far as I know Lighthouse and Teku do not do any of that and it's not spec-ed.\r\n\r\n```\r\nJun-04 03:10:53.117 [NETWORK]       \u001B[36mverbose\u001B[39m: Req  error method=goodbye, encoding=ssz_snappy, agentVersion=teku/teku/v21.4.1/linux-x86_64/-ubuntu-openjdk64bitservervm-java-11, peer=16...kCrRcF, requestId=483 code=REQUEST_ERROR_EMPTY_RESPONSE\r\nError: REQUEST_ERROR_EMPTY_RESPONSE\r\n    at /usr/app/packages/lodestar/src/network/reqresp/request/collectResponses.ts:20:13\r\n    at runMicrotasks (<anonymous>)\r\n    at processTicksAndRejections (internal/process/task_queues.js:93:5)\r\n    at withTimeout (/usr/app/packages/utils/src/timeout.ts:20:12)\r\n    at sendRequest (/usr/app/packages/lodestar/src/network/reqresp/request/index.ts:139:25)\r\n    at ReqResp.sendRequest (/usr/app/packages/lodestar/src/network/reqresp/reqResp.ts:141:22)\r\n    at ReqResp.goodbye (/usr/app/packages/lodestar/src/network/reqresp/reqResp.ts:90:5)\r\n    at PeerManager.goodbyeAndDisconnect (/usr/app/packages/lodestar/src/network/peers/peerManager.ts:429:7)\r\nJun-04 03:10:53.119 [NETWORK]       \u001B[36mverbose\u001B[39m: Failed to send goodbye peer=16...kCrRcF method=goodbye, encoding=ssz_snappy, peer=16...kCrRcF, code=REQUEST_ERROR_EMPTY_RESPONSE\r\nError: REQUEST_ERROR_EMPTY_RESPONSE\r\n    at sendRequest (/usr/app/packages/lodestar/src/network/reqresp/request/index.ts:176:13)\r\n    at runMicrotasks (<anonymous>)\r\n    at processTicksAndRejections (internal/process/task_queues.js:93:5)\r\n    at ReqResp.sendRequest (/usr/app/packages/lodestar/src/network/reqresp/reqResp.ts:141:22)\r\n    at ReqResp.goodbye (/usr/app/packages/lodestar/src/network/reqresp/reqResp.ts:90:5)\r\n    at PeerManager.goodbyeAndDisconnect (/usr/app/packages/lodestar/src/network/peers/peerManager.ts:429:7)\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n\r\n We should not expect that to happen, and not log it as errors.",
